
[1]formally

   FORM'ALLY, adv.

   1. According to established form, rule, order, rite or ceremony. A
   treaty was concluded and formally ratified by both parties.

   2. Ceremoniously; stiffly; precisely; as, to be stiff and formally
   reserved.

   3. In open appearance; in a visible and apparent state.

   You and your followers do stand formally divided against the authorized
   guides of the church, and the rest of the people.

   4. Essentially; characteristically.

   That which formally makes this [charity] a christian grace, is the
   spring from which it flows.
